Others are still open, and are asking the community to support them by ordering pick-up or delivery, and making sure to tip the staff as much as they can.
Jessica Powers, spokeswoman for the restaurant, said the response from the community had been amazing.
Contribute to local social service organizationsThere are plenty of groups and organizations helping those negatively impacted by coronavirus.
Paul Ash, executive director of the San Francisco-Marin Food Bank, said they are especially in need of volunteers in their warehouses and people who can help them open additional pantries.
Reach out to family and friendsSimply reaching out to those most severely affected by coronavirus can be a big help in such a turbulent time.